ramsey/uuid.name: ramsey/uuid
ramsey/uuid.description: A PHP library for generating and working with universally unique identifiers (UUIDs).

suggest.ext-bcmath: Enables faster math with arbitrary-precision integers using BCMath.
suggest.ext-ctype: Enables faster processing of character classification using ctype functions.
suggest.ext-gmp: Enables faster math with arbitrary-precision integers using GMP.
suggest.ext-uuid: Enables the use of PeclUuidTimeGenerator and PeclUuidRandomGenerator.
suggest.paragonie/random-lib: Provides RandomLib for use with the RandomLibAdapter
suggest.ramsey/uuid-doctrine: Allows the use of Ramsey\Uuid\Uuid as Doctrine field type.

ramsey/uuid.description: Formerly rhumsaa/uuid. A PHP 5.4+ library for generating RFC 4122 version 1, 3, 4, and 5 universally unique identifiers (UUID).

suggest.ext-ctype: Provides support for PHP Ctype functions
suggest.ext-libsodium: Provides the PECL libsodium extension for use with the SodiumRandomGenerator
suggest.ext-openssl: Provides the OpenSSL extension for use with the OpenSslGenerator
suggest.ext-uuid: Provides the PECL UUID extension for use with the PeclUuidTimeGenerator and PeclUuidRandomGenerator
suggest.moontoast/math: Provides support for converting UUID to 128-bit integer (in string form).
suggest.ramsey/uuid-console: A console application for generating UUIDs with ramsey/uuid
suggest.ramsey/uuid-doctrine: Allows the use of Ramsey\Uuid\Uuid as Doctrine field type.
suggest.paragonie/random-lib: Provides RandomLib for use with the RandomLibAdapter
